security: Zod request validation on auth/order/payment routes

- New middlewares/validate.js runs a Zod schema against req.body, replies
  400 with field-level errors on failure, and replaces req.body with the
  parsed result so controllers see only schema-defined fields
- New schemas/ dir with authSchemas, orderSchemas, paymentSchemas
- Wired up on: admin/seller/customer login + register, change-password,
  profile-info-add, place-order, paynow create + mobile, withdrawal
  request, payment-request confirm
- paynow/result webhook is not validated because the body shape is
  Paynow's, not ours
- place_order schema still accepts userId from the body (with a note) —
  replacing it with req.user.id is a server-side authorization change
  that belongs to Phase 3
- Drop the now-redundant ad-hoc checks in change_password

